een building since late June. Price carved out a multi-week base in the 0.6865\u20130.6895 area following a sharp sell-off that dragged the pair from above 0.7000 down to lows near 0.6865 across the 23rd and 24th of June. From that floor, the pair has constructed a sequence of higher lows, with the recovery gathering genuine momentum on 14\u201315 July when a strong two-day advance reclaimed the 0.6970s and pushed briefly above 0.7020. That move stalled almost immediately, and the subsequent pullback over 16\u201319 July has been orderly rather than impulsive, which is broadly consistent with consolidation rather than distribution. The pair has spent the past several sessions digesting those gains in a relatively tight range between 0.6960 and 0.7010, which keeps the medium-term recovery narrative intact for now \u2014 though it has not yet been confirmed with a clean daily close above 0.7000.\n\nThe key zones are well-defined. Immediately overhead, the 0.7184 prior reaction zone remains the structural ceiling of note on the daily timeframe, though it is some distance away. More immediately relevant is the 0.6989 area, which aligns loosely with the structure support zone identified at 0.6989. Below that, the 0.6959 prior reaction zone has registered three touches and represents the first meaningful demand area should the current consolidation give way. Deeper still, the 0.6864 zone \u2014 also with three prior touches \u2014 would represent a significant structural deterioration if revisited.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the intraday picture is constructive in the near term. Price dipped to 0.6964 during the early European session before recovering steadily through the morning, posting a sequence of higher hourly lows from 0.6975 upward and reaching 0.6995 into the early afternoon. The recovery from the 0.6964 low has been measured and consistent, suggesting short-term demand is present in the mid-0.6960s. The 0.7000 area is now the immediate intraday reference \u2014 a clean hourly close above it would shift the short-term tone more decisively.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes an obvious catalyst for a directional break. Absent a data shock, price action is likely to remain range-bound around the 0.7000 level, with liquidity thinner than usual. That said, quiet sessions can occasionally produce sharper moves when positioning becomes stretched.\n\nThe bullish recovery read would be undermined on a daily close back below the 0.6959 prior reaction zone, which would suggest the consolidation has tipped into something more corrective. Sustained trade beneath 0.6864 would call the entire recovery structure into question.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}